OL,4,CBedford: Father and son jailed for
OL,5,C#1.7m antiques theft
OL,6, A father and son who stole #1.7m worth
OL,7, of antiques from the home of an elderly
OL,8, widow have been jailed.
OL,10,FDes, 83, and Gary Pickersgill, 42, sold
OL,11,Fitems including Chinese jade and ivory
OL,12,Fornaments, taken from the 96-year-old
OL,13,Fwoman's home near Bedford.
OL,15,FThey were both found guilty of theft,
OL,16,Fwith the father sentenced to six years
OL,17,Fin prison and his son to eight years.
OL,19,FDes Pickersgill encouraged the woman to
OL,20,Fdrink so the thefts would not be
OL,21,Fnoticed, Luton Crown Court heard.
